macro.title: Optimal Blue mortgage data shows 50% refi jump in January as rates dip
macro.what: Falling mortgage rates in January 2026 pushed refinance volume up 50% and increased the VA lending share, per Optimal Blue data.
macro.why: Rates & inflation shape discount rates and housing affordability.
macro.market: Lower rates support demand/valuations; higher rates pressure builders/REITs and slow transactions.

housing.title: Austin, TX—Once Among the Nation’s Hottest Housing Markets—Is Now the Slowest
housing.what: The typical Austin home that went under contract in December spent a record 106 days on the market, compared with 60 days nationwide
housing.why: Price trend signals wealth effects and buyer/seller power.
